              The default layout since 1984. Outdated for modern French: no accented capitals,
              missing several French characters, developer symbols very hard to
              access.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">US International QWERTY</h3>
            <p class="card__text text-secondary">
              The classic workaround for English speakers: good programming symbols and dead-key
              accents for Western European languages. But no œ, apostrophe and quotes become
              dead keys, and nothing matches the keys printed on French keyboards.
            </p>
          </div>

